basic.description: Synthesize the competencies essential to advanced nursing practice to provide primary health care for clients across the life span. Demonstrate autonomy, decision-making, and critical analysis of organizational and system issues that influence scope of practice, professional accountability, and outcomes. Prequisite: All NP courses; Total Course Hours: 455, Seminar: 6 hours every two weeks for a total of 39 seminar hours, Clinical 35 hrs/week for 13 weeks for a total of 416 hours. Summer term.
basic.subject: NURS
basic.title: Integrative Practicum
